'''Tate Jinja''' (建神社) is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|ja|神社|12=draft|12=draft}} located in {{ill|Tsurugi, Tokushima|ja|つるぎ町|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Tokushima Prefecture|ja|徳島県|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== History == The year of its foundation is unknown. It is affectionately called Gongen-san or Gongen-han. According to one theory, it was once located in a place called Tenno in Handayama in ancient times.<ref>{{Cite web|和書|url=https://genbu.net/data/awa2/tate2_title.htm|title=建神社|publisher=玄松子の記憶|accessdate=2021-05-14}}</ref>
It is one of the candidate shrines identified as the Shikinaisha “Tate Jinja.”
== deity == * {{ill|Susanoo-no-Mikoto|ja|素盞嗚命|12=draft|12=draft}}
== Access == * About 10 minutes on foot from {{ill|Awa-Handa Station|ja|阿波半田駅|12=draft|12=draft}} on the {{ill|Tokushima Line|ja|徳島線|12=draft|12=draft}} of {{ill|JR Shikoku|ja|四国旅客鉄道|12=draft|12=draft}}.
